.TH LLC 1 "April 2025" "llc 2.0.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
llc \- enhanced ls command with file comments support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B llc
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B llc
is an enhanced version of \fBls -l\fR that displays file comments at the end of each line.
.PP
On Linux, comments are stored in xattr extended attributes (user.llc.comment).
On macOS, comments are stored in Spotlight metadata (kMDItemFinderComment).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-a
Show all files including hidden files (. and ..)
.TP
.BR \-A
Show all files including hidden files (except . and ..)
.TP
.BR \-1
Single column output (one filename per line)
.TP
.BR \-i
Show file inode numbers
.TP
.BR \-d
List directory itself instead of contents
.TP
.BR \-h
Display file sizes in human-readable format (KB, MB, GB)
.TP
.BR \-F
Add type indicators after filenames (/ for directories, * for executables, @ for symlinks, = for sockets, | for FIFOs)
.TP
.BR \-L
Follow symbolic links and display target file information
.TP
.BR \-t
Sort by modification time (newest first)
.TP
.BR \-u
Sort by access time
.TP
.BR \-U
Sort by creation time
.TP
.BR \-S
Sort by file size (largest first)
.TP
.BR \-\-sort\-ext
Sort by file extension
.TP
.BR \-r
Reverse sort order
.TP
.BR \-R
List subdirectories recursively
.TP
.BR \-\-tree
Display directory contents in a tree-like format
.TP
.BR \-\-json
Output in JSON format
.TP
.BR \-\-csv
Output in CSV format
.TP
.BR \-\-group\-directories\-first
List directories before files
.TP
.BR \-\-ignore\=\fIPATTERN\fR
Ignore files matching the pattern (supports * and ? wildcards)
.TP
.BR \-\-gitignore
Use .gitignore rules from the directory
.TP
.BR \-\-time\-style\=\fISTYLE\fR
Time display format: default, iso, long-iso, full-iso
.TP
.BR \-\-color\=\fIWHEN\fR
Color output: always, auto, never
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-color
Disable color output
.TP
.BR \-e \fIFILE\fR \fI"COMMENT"\fR
Set a comment for the specified file
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Display version information
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
Configuration can be stored in ~/.llcrc:
.PP
.nf
color = auto
sort = name
group-directories-first = true
human-readable = true
show-hidden = false
time-style = default
ignore = *.log
ignore = *.tmp
.fi
.SH COLOR CODES
.TP
.B Blue bold
Directories
.TP
.B Green
Executable files
.TP
.B Cyan
Symbolic links
.TP
.B Gray
File comments
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List current directory:
.B llc
.TP
Show all files including hidden:
.B llc -a
.TP
Human-readable sizes, sorted by time:
.B llc -ht
.TP
Recursive tree view:
.B llc --tree
.TP
JSON output:
.B llc --json
.TP
Set file comment:
.B llc -e file.txt "Important document"
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ls (1),
.BR getfattr (1),
.BR setfattr (1)
